originalText.text:
My wife and I had our first visit here and as first time parents they have done nothing but make us feel comfortable. They never made us feel young, uneducated, or unwanted. It was a much more enjoyable experience than a regular doctors office visit. They answered every question we had and basically begged us to ask more! So informative, the ambiance is incredible, light, airy, and the decor is all very aesthetically pleasing and with a style of its own. We can’t wait to have our next appointment and we will definitely plan to use their services for our second baby as well!

The virtual intake was a breeze and the person we spoke with was great, also extremely informative and let us know to ask our insurance some important questions as well as gave us referrals for the testing we needed to do before coming in.

Waiting area is great and they make dads feel welcome too.

originalText.text: Left a busy OBGYN practice I’ve been going to for 13 years after being talked down to by the OB. Oula was recommended by a friend — we are 8 months in and the experience has been attentive, responsive and thoughtful. I never feel rushed even when I have come in with many questions. Incredibly grateful to be working with this team for my first!

originalText.text: I absolutely love Oula. The care I get for every appointment is amazing! You might have to wait a few (even though the waiting room is usually empty) because of the level of attention the providers give you. They are attentive, compassionate and knowledgeable. Cheryl and all of the other nurses and medical assistants are so sweet. The intake professional at the front desk is super friendly and helpful (I think her name is Ashley). You get to meet all their providers throughout your pregnancy (I am sixteen weeks and have met three so far). The office is so aesthetically pleasing. I travel from New Jersey because of all the great things I heard and have now experience. We need more Oula locations.

originalText.text:
Now that I've completed my journey with Oula, I can write a comprehensive review.

I loved Oula from start to end. I had transferred at the end of my second trimester after a horrible experience with my first OB and then being abroad a couple months.

Coming to Oula was like a sigh of relief. I was listened to, I had choices, I was genuinely cared for. I love that Oula has the Fresh Test option for the glucose tolerance or the option to monitor with glucometer. I chose Fresh Test as it was super easy.

The office is definitely warming, the comfy couches, the welcoming receptionist with water and snacks! My previous OB claimed a spa-like environment but it honestly had nothing. Oula was actually wonderful to visit and sit in the waiting room, although you never wait long! I have never even finished a snack before being called back.

Every nurse I met along the way was wonderful. I'm an anxious patient and the nurses talked to me and always made me laugh and smile. The midwives are nothing short of amazing. They all **spent ample time with me**. As someone with questions and concerns, they never dismissed me or cut me short. They always looked into things and offered full explanations. AND they followed up with me every time.

My labor was terrible, I had prodromal contractions for 5 days before the real deal and showed up to the hospital 7 cm dilated and was shocked since I was going to ask for an induction I was so tired. Although the hospital took forever to get me into the room and the postpartum nurses at Mount Sinai were actually quite terrible, my Oula midwives that delivered my baby and came to check on me postpartum were still amazing.

The postpartum checks with Oula were also very reassuring. I had a third degree tear so I had a 2 week check up to make sure I was healing well. I had pretty bad postpartum depression and the midwife spent a whole hour with me going through everything and offering multiple suggestions and following up with me twice after I left. I had another virtual visit before my in person 6 week check up for lactation help and another lengthy helpful 6 week visit.

I was super sad that was the end of my Oula journey. It almost makes me want to have another baby just so I can have the entire pregnancy journey with them this time!

So happy to hear they are extending for more OB care!

10/10 recommend Oula!
Also I have Oscar insurance and only needed to pay $100 for everything.

originalText.text: I hopefully never have to seek prenatal care and deliver with another team in the future, because OULA is simply the best! The receptionist welcomes you with a smile and is so personable. The midwives are all incredibly informative, sweet, and professional. They provide evidenced-based practice while also listening and addressing all your concerns. They're committed to making sure you come as close to your birth vision as possible. I gave birth to a healthy baby boy (thank you Sarah!) and am so appreciative and thankful for the care I received during the whole process.
